						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja I. Year 19: 1003-04 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and mutilated. It begins with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> commencing with <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> etc., and mentions Iḍaiyaḷa-nāḍu.</p>						

